1
00:00:05,553 --> 00:00:07,634
All right, so my name is Bruno Velasquez.

2
00:00:07,814 --> 00:00:10,556
I'm the Animation Director at Sony Santa Monica.

3
00:00:11,736 --> 00:00:14,378
I've been with the studio since 2006,

4
00:00:14,438 --> 00:00:17,560
so I had a long relationship with Kratos,

5
00:00:17,700 --> 00:00:18,961
about 13 years or so.

6
00:00:20,001 --> 00:00:22,203
My first game at the studio was God of War II,

7
00:00:22,743 --> 00:00:25,184
and that was a great experience,

8
00:00:25,244 --> 00:00:28,246
working with Cory Barlog as Game Director,

9
00:00:28,326 --> 00:00:30,147
and for this latest project,

10
00:00:30,527 --> 00:00:32,088
had the opportunity to work with him again,

11
00:00:32,168 --> 00:00:32,649
which was great.

12
00:00:33,729 --> 00:00:35,610
This is my first animation bootcamp,

13
00:00:35,690 --> 00:00:37,771
so this is amazing that I get to be here

14
00:00:37,791 --> 00:00:40,932
with all of you guys, talk about animation.

15
00:00:41,192 --> 00:00:42,713
It's amazing, I'm so happy to be here.

16
00:00:42,753 --> 00:00:43,713
So thank you for having me.

17
00:00:44,614 --> 00:00:47,395
And the name of my talk is God of War,

18
00:00:47,655 --> 00:00:49,616
Breathing New Life into a Hardened Spartan.

19
00:00:51,404 --> 00:00:55,328
So God of War, it's a franchise from Sony.

20
00:00:56,389 --> 00:00:58,551
It's on the eighth game now.

21
00:00:59,472 --> 00:01:01,093
The latest one came out last year.

22
00:01:01,874 --> 00:01:06,058
And it centers around a Spartan named Kratos.

23
00:01:07,259 --> 00:01:08,820
The first seven games pretty much

24
00:01:09,481 --> 00:01:11,403
delved into Greek mythology.

25
00:01:12,784 --> 00:01:14,325
And the latest one, we decided to take it

26
00:01:14,365 --> 00:01:15,426
into the Norse realm.

27
00:01:16,384 --> 00:01:19,606
Now, one of the biggest things when Corey Barlog first

28
00:01:20,006 --> 00:01:23,569
set off to give us the mission on how we were going

29
00:01:23,589 --> 00:01:26,191
to make this game, one of the challenges for animation

30
00:01:26,271 --> 00:01:28,613
was how we're going to reimagine Kratos.

31
00:01:28,973 --> 00:01:30,494
How are we going to present him in a new light?

32
00:01:31,475 --> 00:01:34,977
We kind of wanted to not completely throw everything

33
00:01:35,057 --> 00:01:36,438
away that we did in the past before,

34
00:01:36,618 --> 00:01:39,240
but we want to kind of depict him in a new light,

35
00:01:39,621 --> 00:01:42,443
present him in a new way for new audiences,

36
00:01:42,803 --> 00:01:45,845
and also to please the fans that had been with us for so long.

37
00:01:48,027 --> 00:01:50,990
So our first mission was to reimagine Kratos.

38
00:01:51,831 --> 00:01:52,672
How were we gonna do that?

39
00:01:53,793 --> 00:01:56,476
So most everybody knows Kratos this way.

40
00:01:57,497 --> 00:01:59,439
They remember him from previous games

41
00:02:00,240 --> 00:02:03,703
in a path of vengeance and rage and destruction.

42
00:02:05,245 --> 00:02:08,328
You know, that was his mission, right?

43
00:02:08,388 --> 00:02:10,430
It was to get revenge, to get payback from the gods.

44
00:02:13,191 --> 00:02:16,572
So in order to kind of change a little bit

45
00:02:16,592 --> 00:02:19,573
of that perception, we needed to focus on the humanity.

46
00:02:19,833 --> 00:02:21,734
So we need to make a conscious effort

47
00:02:22,734 --> 00:02:25,435
on how we're gonna show more of the human side of Kratos.

48
00:02:26,276 --> 00:02:28,036
So from an animation standpoint,

49
00:02:28,056 --> 00:02:30,397
that was a very interesting challenge for us.

50
00:02:32,398 --> 00:02:35,719
So when you think of a character like the Hulk,

51
00:02:37,040 --> 00:02:39,380
I had to make my own drawing just to be safe.

52
00:02:39,400 --> 00:02:42,401
Don't wanna make anybody mad at me.

53
00:02:44,037 --> 00:02:46,440
But when you think of a character like the Hulk,

54
00:02:46,680 --> 00:02:48,302
you know, there's two sides of him, right?

55
00:02:48,722 --> 00:02:50,965
There's the Hulk side, the angry green guy,

56
00:02:51,045 --> 00:02:53,107
and then there's Banner, there's the human side.

57
00:02:53,848 --> 00:02:58,113
So what we needed to do was explore that for Kratos, you know.

58
00:02:59,045 --> 00:03:00,265
Those Kratos, what about Kratos?

59
00:03:00,325 --> 00:03:02,007
Does Kratos have that side?

60
00:03:02,487 --> 00:03:03,587
Or is he all just full of rage?

61
00:03:04,708 --> 00:03:06,309
So if you look back into the previous games,

62
00:03:06,889 --> 00:03:08,871
there were little glimpses of that humanity.

63
00:03:09,551 --> 00:03:10,612
We didn't show them very often,

64
00:03:10,632 --> 00:03:11,512
but there was a little bit, right?

65
00:03:13,073 --> 00:03:14,854
He at one point wanted to save his brother,

66
00:03:16,855 --> 00:03:18,657
wanted to rescue him once he found out

67
00:03:18,697 --> 00:03:19,497
that he was still alive.

68
00:03:20,878 --> 00:03:23,159
His brother Deimos was, fought alongside with him

69
00:03:23,179 --> 00:03:24,680
for a little bit before he lost him again.

70
00:03:26,902 --> 00:03:29,505
There was moments where he showed compassion

71
00:03:29,525 --> 00:03:30,446
and care for his family,

72
00:03:32,208 --> 00:03:36,793
even though he ended up tragically by mistake killing them.

73
00:03:37,574 --> 00:03:40,737
But there was glimpses there that he missed them,

74
00:03:41,298 --> 00:03:43,400
he wanted to embrace them and be with them once again.

75
00:03:44,461 --> 00:03:47,424
And of course, the moment of regret and remorse

76
00:03:47,504 --> 00:03:49,306
where he pretty much wanted to end it all.

77
00:03:50,314 --> 00:03:52,616
He wanted to move on, he couldn't deal with it.

78
00:03:52,896 --> 00:03:57,759
So definitely, as much as we showed moments of power

79
00:03:57,799 --> 00:03:59,980
and strength in Kratos, there was also a little bit

80
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:03,582
of the human side kind of sprinkled throughout the games.

81
00:04:04,223 --> 00:04:07,305
You know, it wasn't all about ripping people's heads off.

82
00:04:08,145 --> 00:04:11,848
Well, actually, it kind of was, most of the time, right?

83
00:04:12,508 --> 00:04:15,230
But we had to basically ask ourselves,

84
00:04:15,250 --> 00:04:18,412
how are we gonna go from this to something like this?

85
00:04:19,198 --> 00:04:23,200
where Curtis is gonna be a teacher, a mentor, a protector.

86
00:04:24,681 --> 00:04:29,144
That was just something that we hadn't done much of before.

87
00:04:31,485 --> 00:04:32,706
So one of the first things that we did

88
00:04:32,946 --> 00:04:35,988
is we looked at his proportions.

89
00:04:37,771 --> 00:04:40,633
If we wanted to have someone that people can sympathize

90
00:04:40,673 --> 00:04:44,936
with more, we need to revisit the way he looked a bit.

91
00:04:45,776 --> 00:04:47,257
This is Kratos from the previous games.

92
00:04:47,997 --> 00:04:50,519
The proportions are a bit wacky, I gotta admit.

93
00:04:50,579 --> 00:04:54,021
He's got super long arms, super long legs, a tiny head.

94
00:04:54,041 --> 00:04:56,723
I mean, look at his hands.

95
00:04:56,843 --> 00:04:57,944
He can crush his own head.

96
00:04:58,244 --> 00:05:00,945
Just, it's a little bit off, right?

97
00:05:01,486 --> 00:05:05,828
But in the end, for what we needed these proportions for,

98
00:05:05,848 --> 00:05:06,829
it kind of worked out.

99
00:05:07,815 --> 00:05:11,056
You know, we were going for more of this comic book

100
00:05:11,916 --> 00:05:14,137
over the top style in the previous games.

101
00:05:15,137 --> 00:05:17,298
So those proportions kind of read well

102
00:05:17,358 --> 00:05:18,698
in the poses that we needed him to be.

103
00:05:19,799 --> 00:05:23,100
Not to mention that the perspective of the game

104
00:05:23,420 --> 00:05:24,480
was much farther away.

105
00:05:24,840 --> 00:05:26,181
So he needed to read a lot clearer.

106
00:05:26,681 --> 00:05:27,882
So those proportions worked well.

107
00:05:29,320 --> 00:05:30,881
Now, one of the first things I did,

108
00:05:31,981 --> 00:05:34,302
once Corey gave me the direction of like,

109
00:05:34,702 --> 00:05:37,264
well, he's gonna be a father figure,

110
00:05:37,324 --> 00:05:38,124
he's gonna have a son,

111
00:05:39,225 --> 00:05:42,206
so I just kind of scrambled and looked for some old models,

112
00:05:42,506 --> 00:05:44,487
or just grabbed whatever we had at the time

113
00:05:44,728 --> 00:05:45,628
at the beginning of the project,

114
00:05:46,048 --> 00:05:48,790
started posting cradles out in different situations.

115
00:05:49,330 --> 00:05:50,610
In this case, I just grabbed,

116
00:05:50,951 --> 00:05:53,552
actually, that's his brother Demos as a kid.

117
00:05:54,112 --> 00:05:56,654
So it's a little weird to have his younger brother there.

118
00:05:56,755 --> 00:05:59,877
But that was all we had to represent Atreus at the time.

119
00:06:00,758 --> 00:06:04,041
So in these, I kind of just wanted to explore

120
00:06:04,441 --> 00:06:07,464
what it would feel like for Kratos to be a protector.

121
00:06:09,465 --> 00:06:10,727
And also a teacher and a mentor.

122
00:06:12,087 --> 00:06:15,109
So here are some early poses of him teaching his son

123
00:06:15,169 --> 00:06:17,030
how to hunt, how to use the bow.

124
00:06:17,710 --> 00:06:20,692
And also a situation which you would never really see

125
00:06:20,712 --> 00:06:22,654
in the previous games, just sitting down and talking,

126
00:06:22,774 --> 00:06:25,335
having a conversation, eating and drinking.

127
00:06:25,375 --> 00:06:26,636
When did Kratos ever do that, right?

128
00:06:26,676 --> 00:06:29,618
So we wanted to start exploring those things.

129
00:06:29,738 --> 00:06:33,200
But as you can see, the proportions, you know,

130
00:06:33,261 --> 00:06:35,782
the old models, yeah, it still was a little bit off.

131
00:06:37,883 --> 00:06:41,306
So as the script progressed, there was a couple of scenes

132
00:06:41,326 --> 00:06:43,688
that we found out about where Kratos, you know,

133
00:06:43,728 --> 00:06:46,050
the son was gonna be sick at one point.

134
00:06:47,251 --> 00:06:49,734
Kratos had to put his hand on his son's shoulder

135
00:06:50,374 --> 00:06:52,616
at one point, even though it took him a little bit of time

136
00:06:52,656 --> 00:06:53,397
to do that in the game.

137
00:06:54,761 --> 00:06:57,342
He was also meant to carry him at one point in his back

138
00:06:58,603 --> 00:06:59,704
during the climbing sequences.

139
00:06:59,764 --> 00:07:03,326
So I started posting this old models.

140
00:07:03,667 --> 00:07:04,987
And as you can see, yes,

141
00:07:05,108 --> 00:07:06,989
the proportions needed some development

142
00:07:07,689 --> 00:07:09,530
in order for him to feel a little bit more human.

143
00:07:11,352 --> 00:07:13,493
So the Concept Art team started working on that.

144
00:07:14,254 --> 00:07:16,675
As you can see, this is very, some early concept

145
00:07:17,276 --> 00:07:18,376
where he started to,

146
00:07:18,496 --> 00:07:20,458
they started taking inspiration from the previous games

147
00:07:20,518 --> 00:07:21,338
and the way that he looked.

148
00:07:22,832 --> 00:07:23,872
I started adding the beard,

149
00:07:23,912 --> 00:07:26,792
started adding the Norse motifs to him.

150
00:07:28,113 --> 00:07:31,874
And as you can see, he has a bit more of a human proportions,

151
00:07:32,134 --> 00:07:36,115
a little bit closer to a more relatable human.

152
00:07:37,215 --> 00:07:40,576
Even his weapon, as you can see, at the early stages,

153
00:07:40,716 --> 00:07:43,456
there was no, it wasn't a magical axe.

154
00:07:43,596 --> 00:07:46,297
It was just a simple weapon that he was to use.

155
00:07:47,237 --> 00:07:49,958
The direction of the game early on was very grounded.

156
00:07:50,358 --> 00:07:52,198
It was meant to be a lot more realistic.

157
00:07:53,239 --> 00:07:56,482
And in the early beginnings, as I will show you,

158
00:07:57,303 --> 00:08:00,746
some of the early animation was very grounded

159
00:08:00,806 --> 00:08:06,232
and more not as sort of over the top as it ended up being.

160
00:08:06,852 --> 00:08:10,636
So we had to dial that in to make it work

161
00:08:10,716 --> 00:08:11,697
with the direction of the game.

162
00:08:12,638 --> 00:08:13,919
Here's a shot of...

163
00:08:15,275 --> 00:08:17,695
The 3D model, as if it was making progress.

164
00:08:18,475 --> 00:08:24,737
This is around the time of the E3 reveal in 2016.

165
00:08:26,357 --> 00:08:28,038
The first time that we showed Kratos to the public,

166
00:08:28,218 --> 00:08:30,258
the new Kratos emerging from the shadows.

167
00:08:30,298 --> 00:08:32,339
So as you can see already, he was starting to feel

168
00:08:32,359 --> 00:08:38,300
a little more human than how we previously depicted him.

169
00:08:39,980 --> 00:08:42,981
But of course, he needed to, again, interact with his son.

170
00:08:44,567 --> 00:08:49,631
So even though he had more human-like proportions now,

171
00:08:50,812 --> 00:08:53,874
he still needed to feel like a giant amongst men.

172
00:08:54,715 --> 00:08:57,117
So even the interactions with the son,

173
00:08:58,698 --> 00:09:01,360
while they worked in the game, he was still a pretty large man.

174
00:09:04,456 --> 00:09:07,577
The next thing that we needed to look into was posing.

175
00:09:08,397 --> 00:09:11,178
How are we gonna create our poses in our animation

176
00:09:11,858 --> 00:09:14,299
to best depict Kratos in this new light?

177
00:09:15,139 --> 00:09:19,881
Older, grounded, sort of more weathered warrior.

178
00:09:22,141 --> 00:09:24,922
So looking back at the previous games,

179
00:09:25,362 --> 00:09:28,863
this is some of the poses that we went for more

180
00:09:31,144 --> 00:09:33,024
heavy metal magazine cover.

181
00:09:34,083 --> 00:09:36,184
type of look, comic book over the top.

182
00:09:36,804 --> 00:09:38,325
And many of these poses, what's interesting

183
00:09:38,385 --> 00:09:39,966
about these poses is that many of these poses

184
00:09:40,006 --> 00:09:41,487
were done by the animators.

185
00:09:41,767 --> 00:09:47,330
So we did not really want other teams,

186
00:09:47,370 --> 00:09:49,331
like marketing teams working on our poses

187
00:09:49,551 --> 00:09:51,453
as much as possible, because we wanted to maintain

188
00:09:52,673 --> 00:09:54,914
the feel of the character throughout, even in marketing.

189
00:09:55,495 --> 00:09:58,336
So I'm sure many of you guys have spent so much time

190
00:09:58,717 --> 00:10:01,538
posing, developing base poses for your characters,

191
00:10:02,058 --> 00:10:02,719
combat poses.

192
00:10:03,359 --> 00:10:05,100
And then all of a sudden, marketing comes back

193
00:10:05,140 --> 00:10:08,642
with these T-shirts, and you're like, wait, who made that pose?

194
00:10:08,662 --> 00:10:09,362
Where did that come from?

195
00:10:10,002 --> 00:10:12,164
And that's pretty horrifying.

196
00:10:12,304 --> 00:10:14,805
So we definitely wanted to maintain that

197
00:10:15,225 --> 00:10:19,127
across not only the game, but marketing materials as well.

198
00:10:20,668 --> 00:10:23,729
So taking this concept of these over-the-top poses,

199
00:10:24,410 --> 00:10:27,892
we needed to apply those to our older, hardened Spartan.

200
00:10:29,384 --> 00:10:33,650
So while we did not push it as far as we did in the previous games,

201
00:10:34,271 --> 00:10:35,393
we still had hints of that.

202
00:10:35,413 --> 00:10:38,739
As you can see in his blocking post, still

203
00:10:39,139 --> 00:10:41,844
needed to be dynamic and strong and grounded,

204
00:10:42,104 --> 00:10:43,626
but a little more grounded than before.

205
00:10:44,548 --> 00:10:47,210
And even when he interacts with enemies and kills them,

206
00:10:48,251 --> 00:10:49,572
yes, it's a bit over the top,

207
00:10:49,612 --> 00:10:51,653
but it's a little bit more grounded

208
00:10:51,673 --> 00:10:52,634
than it used to be before.

209
00:10:52,995 --> 00:10:54,376
So we needed to keep that in mind

210
00:10:54,856 --> 00:10:57,618
as we were posing anything that had to do with Kratos,

211
00:10:57,859 --> 00:11:00,781
you know, animation, combat, idols, anything.

212
00:11:02,362 --> 00:11:05,245
He's not quite as hunched down as he used to be overall.

213
00:11:05,425 --> 00:11:06,426
That was one of the main things.

214
00:11:06,766 --> 00:11:08,567
We didn't want to get him as slow

215
00:11:08,768 --> 00:11:10,349
as he was in the previous games.

216
00:11:13,607 --> 00:11:17,530
Another aspect of grounding Kratos was Atreus.

217
00:11:18,672 --> 00:11:21,835
So Kratos was there to help his son teach him

218
00:11:21,875 --> 00:11:24,157
how to be a god, how to be a warrior, how to survive.

219
00:11:24,877 --> 00:11:27,100
But at the same time, the importance of Atreus

220
00:11:27,480 --> 00:11:29,782
was there to make Kratos feel more human.

221
00:11:30,783 --> 00:11:32,765
In the previous games, Kratos would walk around

222
00:11:32,785 --> 00:11:36,388
and meet people and maybe say a word

223
00:11:36,609 --> 00:11:38,390
and then kill them most of the time.

224
00:11:39,331 --> 00:11:42,236
So we needed to have an emotional anchor.

225
00:11:43,498 --> 00:11:46,584
Atreus was basically there to be the eyes

226
00:11:47,065 --> 00:11:48,287
and the voice of the player.

227
00:11:48,788 --> 00:11:49,830
Kratos would not...

228
00:11:50,805 --> 00:11:58,151
when he would travel in the previous games, he didn't wonder where this statue came from or

229
00:11:58,531 --> 00:12:05,176
what it said, what message was written on the wall. So by presenting Atreus and then

230
00:12:05,556 --> 00:12:08,718
partnering him up with Kratos, we were able to, you know...

231
00:12:09,439 --> 00:12:14,182
sort of get conversations actually happening between two characters, which just didn't happen

232
00:12:14,222 --> 00:12:20,987
before. And this way, our goal was for the player to get to know Kratos a little more and to get

233
00:12:21,027 --> 00:12:25,210
Kratos out of his comfort zone. And by having a young son there that he needed to look after and

234
00:12:25,230 --> 00:12:29,313
interact with, that was, it offered a lot of opportunities for us to do that.

235
00:12:31,198 --> 00:12:33,079
Now, a bit of the studio culture too.

236
00:12:34,200 --> 00:12:38,443
You know, as the studio grew and the team grew, so did we.

237
00:12:39,304 --> 00:12:41,926
And many of the team members became parents,

238
00:12:42,086 --> 00:12:43,347
we got married, had kids.

239
00:12:44,328 --> 00:12:47,890
And that kind of changed the way we saw things, you know?

240
00:12:48,291 --> 00:12:51,173
We wanted to tell different types of stories as well.

241
00:12:51,333 --> 00:12:52,954
So this was part of the big influence

242
00:12:52,994 --> 00:12:53,975
of why we decided to...

243
00:12:55,896 --> 00:12:58,538
re-imagine creatives and make them more relatable.

244
00:12:59,859 --> 00:13:01,400
Previously it was like the Greek era,

245
00:13:01,521 --> 00:13:04,063
it was kind of like the college years, right?

246
00:13:05,023 --> 00:13:07,045
You know, having a little more fun.

247
00:13:07,885 --> 00:13:09,687
Well, you know, not that we're not having fun still,

248
00:13:10,067 --> 00:13:12,809
but the Norse era is a bit more like,

249
00:13:12,909 --> 00:13:17,253
okay, you know, let's try to tell some different stories

250
00:13:17,293 --> 00:13:19,274
that, you know, perhaps we can share

