00:42:00,959 --> 00:42:03,601
it definitely was what got us over the top

801
00:42:03,981 --> 00:42:04,782
to be able to.

802
00:42:06,114 --> 00:42:07,203
to make this into a...

803
00:42:09,147 --> 00:42:12,327
a weapon that would stand side to side with the blades.

804
00:42:12,947 --> 00:42:15,308
And in addition to that, the history of the axe

805
00:42:15,448 --> 00:42:17,688
was that it was given to him by his wife,

806
00:42:18,449 --> 00:42:21,369
rather than being given to him by a god

807
00:42:21,389 --> 00:42:24,090
for as a weapon of destruction, right?

808
00:42:24,110 --> 00:42:26,270
So it was more of a weapon of protection,

809
00:42:27,090 --> 00:42:28,871
given to him by his own wife.

810
00:42:29,411 --> 00:42:32,592
So already the story behind the weapon was different,

811
00:42:32,752 --> 00:42:35,792
to try to make him feel a little more connected to it

812
00:42:35,832 --> 00:42:38,053
in a different way than anger and rage.

